{"type":"message","id":"5653f4e7","parentId":"96ae609c","timestamp":"2026-05-30T07:42:15.207Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user (汀桑) is saying they're configuring a new user through the QQ bot channel, and asking if I can handle it directly here, since they set permissions. They're saying they set up some access controls/permissions.\n\nLet me think about this. They're asking if they can directly configure/onboard a new user through this conversation. They mentioned they set permissions - probably referring to the permission/approval system in OpenClaw.\n\nLet me check what's going on with permissions. I think they might be referring to the fact that when they try to do something that requires approval (like elevated exec commands), they need to approve it. Let me check the current permission setup.\n\nActually, I think they're saying they set up some kind of permission or approval mechanism, and they're asking if they can directly configure the new user from this conversation without needing extra approval steps.\n\nLet me just respond naturally - they're asking about whether they can handle the new user setup directly through this chat since they already have permissions configured.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"你设过啥权限了？我这头没啥特别的限制——要是涉及改系统配置那些需要弹审批的操作，你点个 `/approve` 就行。\n\n新用户配置你打算怎么搞？直接让 ta 加 bot QQ 就行，还是你要先搭个什么注册流程？\n\n你说了算，我配合🍧"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":603,"output":278,"cacheRead":25216,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":208,"totalTokens":26097,"cost":{"input":0.00008442000000000001,"output":0.00007784,"cacheRead":0.000706048,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000868308}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780126931396,"responseId":"dd5dca27-727c-4169-af28-d458c42160c8"}}
