{"type":"message","id":"35a4777d","parentId":"883bc763","timestamp":"2026-05-30T07:45:22.331Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"汀桑 is saying that the current bot1 (appid:1904097640) seems to be limited to only him/her - perhaps because the QQ bot was configured with their QQ as the admin/message receiver, or there's some configuration limitation.\n\nLet me think about this... If bot1 is currently set up to only work with 汀桑's QQ account (6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204), then to onboard a new user, they need either:\n1. A second QQ bot account (bot2) configured\n2. Or to change bot1's config to accept messages from any QQ user\n\nThis is a gateway configuration thing - I can look at the config schema to see how QQ bot user filtering works.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"噢——懂了。你现在这个 bot1 只有你能用，是配成了仅接受你一个人的消息？\n\n那我看看网关配置能不能调。先看看当前怎么设的。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_1bcz9XT8FgCJBCRADGE18801","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/config.yaml 2>/dev/null || cat /root/.openclaw/gateway.yaml 2>/dev/null || openclaw gateway config.schema.lookup --path='qqbot' 2>&1 | head -80"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat /root/.openclaw/config.yaml 2>/dev/null || cat /root/.openclaw/gateway.yaml 2>/dev/null || openclaw gateway config.schema.lookup --path='qqbot' 2>&1 | head -80\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":551,"output":293,"cacheRead":25600,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":161,"totalTokens":26444,"cost":{"input":0.00007714000000000001,"output":0.00008204000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0007168,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0008759799999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780127118868,"responseId":"2be5c385-74a1-4939-a89d-d571814ad2fe"}}
