{"type":"message","id":"f63bd6f0","parentId":"38fc82b3","timestamp":"2026-05-30T07:45:55.339Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So here's the configuration. I can see:\n\n1. There are **4 QQ bot accounts** configured: bot1, bot2, bot3, bot4\n2. accountId `bot1` has `appId: \"1904085484\"` - **NOT** the appId that 汀桑 mentioned (1904097640)\n3. All 4 bots are routed to `father` agent\n4. Channels config has `\"allowFrom\": [\"*\"]` - meaning all users are allowed\n\nCurrent bot accounts:\n- bot1: 1904085484\n- bot2: 1904088180\n- bot3: 1904090109\n- bot4: 1904093350\n\n汀桑 said `appid:1904097640` - that's NOT one of the currently configured bots. So he might be saying that he's registering a **new** QQ bot with appid 1904097640, and he's wondering if this bot is currently usable by just him.\n\nWait, but looking at the conversation flow more carefully:\n- 汀桑 said \"appid:1904097640\" - that's a new bot not in the config\n- Then I said bot1's appid is 1904085484\n- Then he said the untrusted metadata shows the current session is on bot1\n\nSo 汀桑 sent appid:1904097640 as a new bot he wants to add. But then the system metadata showed the current session is on bot1 (1904085484), and he responded that \"bot1只能我一个人用\" - bot1 only works for me.\n\nWait, I think the confusion is: 汀桑 showed the untrusted metadata to clarify which bot he's talking about. The current session is on bot1. And he's saying:\n\n- He's testing\n- It seems bot1 only accepts messages from him (the sender_id 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204)\n\nBut looking at the config: `\"allowFrom\": [\"*\"]` - that should mean anyone can send messages. Unless there's something in the QQ bot platform itself restricting it.\n\nSo maybe 汀桑 is saying:\n1. He created a new QQ bot (appid:1904097640) \n2. But the current session shows it's bot1 (1904085484)\n3. Bot1 seems to only accept messages from him\n\nActually wait, I think I was confused earlier. Let me re-read:\n\n汀桑 said: \"appid:1904097640\" \nI replied about bot1 having appid 1904085484\nThen the untrusted metadata showed the session is on bot1\nThen 汀桑 said \"目前是测试阶段，好像Bot1只能我一个人用\"\n\nSo I think 汀桑 is asking me to either:\n1. Register the new bot (1904097640) in the config\n2. Or confirm that bot1 is accessible to others\n\nSince `allowFrom: [\"*\"]` is already set, bot1 should accept messages from anyone. The issue might be:\n1. On the QQ platform side - the bot might be in testing/development mode and only accepts messages from developers\n2. Or there's some other restriction\n\n汀桑 might be saying that he's in testing phase and wants to know how to allow other users to access the bot.\n\nActually, re-reading the conversation more carefully:\n\n汀桑 started by saying \"我现在在qqbot途径配置一个新用户\" - I'm configuring a new user on qqbot channel\nThen \"你这里能直接搭吗，我好像设置了权限是吧\" - can you set it up directly here? I think I set some permission.\nThen \"appid:1904097640\" - this is the new app's appid\n\nSo 汀桑 wants to add a new user (person) to access via QQ bot. The appid 1904097640 might be a new bot they registered.\n\nLooking at the config, there's no appid 1904097640 configured. And he said \"bot1只能我一个人用\" - bot1 only works for them.\n\nI think what's happening is: 汀桑 registered a new QQ bot with appid 1904097640 on the QQ platform, and now wants me to add it to the openclaw config so new users can talk to the bot.\n\nBut wait - the current session is on bot1 (1904085484), and he's saying bot1 only works for him. Let me look at the config more carefully...\n\nActually, I think there might be a simpler explanation: 汀桑 is just saying that he's the only one who can message bot1 because the QQ bot hasn't been published/reviewed on the QQ platform yet - it's in sandbox/development mode where only the developer's QQ can send messages.\n\nSo the question is: does he need me to:\nA. Add the new bot (1904097640) to the config as a new account?\nB. Or is he just noting that currently bot1 is in test mode?\n\nLet me just clarify with him - what does he want me to do?\n\nActually, looking at this from a different angle: \n- The current session IS on bot1 (account_id: bot1 in the inbound context)\n- 汀桑 is the one talking to me\n- 汀桑 sent appid:1904097640 which is NOT in the config\n- 汀桑 says \"bot1只能我一个人用\"\n\nSo maybe 汀桑 is:\n1. Registering a new bot with appid 1904097640 on QQ platform\n2. Wants to add it to the OpenClaw config as a new account (bot5?)\n3. So that other users can use THIS new bot to talk to me\n\nOR he wanted me to check if bot1 is already set to accept everyone (it is: allowFrom: [\"*\"]), and the limitation is on QQ's platform side.\n\nLet me just tell him what I found and ask what he wants to do.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"我看到了——\n\n配置里 `allowFrom: [\"*\"]` 已经是允许所有人了，所以网关这头没锁你。**bot1 只能你一个人用** 这个限制看起来是 **QQ 开放平台那边的**——新注册的机器人默认只有开发者账号能发消息，还没过审核上线。\n\n你刚才发那个 **appid:1904097640** 是目前不在配置里的新 bot 对吧？\n\n有两种走法：\n\n**A.** 把这个新 bot（1904097640）加进网关配置——我帮你写进去，弹审批你点一下 `/approve` 就行。新用户加这个 bot QQ 就能直接找我。\n\n**B.** 继续用现有的 bot1/bot2/bot3/bot4，等其中一个上架了再开放给其他人——你发 appid 是让我看看哪个能用？\n\n你是要 A 还是 B？还是你其实已经注册好了 1904097640 这个新 bot，想让我现在配进去🚬"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":3059,"output":1476,"cacheRead":28032,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":1266,"totalTokens":32567,"cost":{"input":0.00042826,"output":0.00041328000000000003,"cacheRead":0.000784896,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001626436}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780127142277,"responseId":"c852beab-f6d5-4d31-85d0-0258c8e10f00"}}
