{"type":"message","id":"959b9b14","parentId":"dbdce00e","timestamp":"2026-05-30T07:46:12.368Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"汀桑 is saying \"腾讯的限制\" - the limitation is from Tencent's side. So the QQ bot platform itself has restrictions - newly registered bots can only receive messages from the developer's QQ account before they go through review/approval on the QQ platform.\n\nSo basically he's telling me that there's nothing I can do on the gateway side - the restriction is on Tencent's end. The bot needs to be reviewed and published on the QQ Open Platform before it can accept messages from other users.\n\nThis makes sense. The QQ bot development mode / sandbox mode only allows the developer's QQ account to interact with it.\n\nSo he's just telling me the situation - not asking me to do anything about it right now. Let me acknowledge this and move on.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"噢，那没招了。腾讯那边的开发模式限制，只有开发者本人的 QQ 能跟机器人对话——审核上架之后才开放给其他人。\n\n所以你刚才发 appid 是在告诉我**新 bot 已经注册好了**，但现在还发不出来，只能你自己先测？\n\n那你的意思是——先这样用着，等 bot 上架了再告诉我开闸放人？还是说你有别的想法👊"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":6225,"output":244,"cacheRead":26368,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":155,"totalTokens":32837,"cost":{"input":0.0008715000000000001,"output":0.00006832000000000001,"cacheRead":0.000738304,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001678124}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780127168851,"responseId":"e14e3e43-0fe6-46fe-bd8c-05cb0a5d1f1c"}}
