{"type":"message","id":"64f754ea","parentId":"9de9e888","timestamp":"2026-05-30T14:32:16.201Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"汀桑 is asking me to look more carefully at the pending_urges push logic that was there before, and what it looked like. They're referring to the AGENTS.md section 5.6 that I just edited. Let me re-read the current state of the file to see what's there now.\n\nActually, they're asking me to look at the original logic that was there before my edits. Let me check if there was previously a section 5.6 or if the logic exists elsewhere.\n\nLooking at the AGENTS.md I edited, the old text that was replaced was:\n- 5.4 写梦\n- 5.5 生成主动说话的念头\n\nThere was no 5.6 section in the original - I added it. The pending_urges cron was set up earlier (the cron job exists) but the push logic in the AGENTS.md was missing - it was only in the cron job's prompt message.\n\nLet me look at the cron job prompt for faye-pending-urges to see the delivery logic that's actually being used:\n\n```\n[pending-urges] 检查 heart/pending_urges.md，处理所有 status=pending 条目。注意：只在 22:00 之前推送。当前时间超过 22:00 则跳过推送，等下次 cron 检查再处理。判断条件：1) min_interval_hours 过了没 2) 对方最近12h有说话吗 3) 熟悉度>=3/10。满足的创建一次性 announce cron（delivery mode=announce, deleteAfterRun=true）推消息给对方，推完标记 delivered。不满足的跳过。全部处理完写回文件。\n```\n\nAnd then the actual cron delivery for the pending_urges was set to announce mode with the target I just added.\n\nBut 汀桑 is asking me to look at what was there BEFORE - specifically the logic about checking whether to push. Let me look at the AGENTS.md file as it was before my edit, or the old state of the cron.\n\nActually wait - looking at the AGENTS.md file that was in the Project Context at the beginning of this session, the section 5.6 was already defined there (it's in the truncated section that was loaded as part of Project Context). Let me re-read what was in that original content.\n\nFrom the Project Context at the start:\n\n```\n### 5.6 pending_urges 推送\n\n由 cron `faye-pending-urges`（每6h触发）处理：\n1. 读 `heart/pending_urges.md`，找所有 `status: pending` 的条目\n2. 判断条件：\n   - min_interval_hours 过了没\n   - 对方最近12h有说话吗\n   - 熟悉度 >= 3/10\n3. 满足条件的：创建一次性 announce cron 推消息给用户，推完标记 `delivered`\n4. 不满足的：跳过，等下次检查\n5. 只在 22:00 之前推送\n```\n\nSo there WAS a 5.6 section already in AGENTS.md! But the dreaming prompt didn't include the step to generate urges. And the pending_urges cron delivery was broken because it didn't have the right target format.\n\n汀桑 is asking me to look more carefully at the delivery logic - specifically the \"检查是否推送\" logic. Let me re-read the cron job prompt more carefully and the AGENTS.md section.\n\nThe original AGENTS.md section 5.6 says:\n1. Read pending_urges.md, find all status: pending\n2. Check:\n   - min_interval_hours passed?\n   - Has the person spoken in the last 12h?\n   - Familiarity >= 3/10?\n3. If yes: create one-time announce cron, push to user, mark delivered\n4. If no: skip, wait for next check\n5. Only push before 22:00\n\nThe cron prompt says similar things but mentions: \"满足的创建一次性 announce cron（delivery mode=announce, deleteAfterRun=true）推消息给对方\"\n\nSo the logic creates a *nested/sub cron* to do the actual push. The pending_urges cron itself is an isolated agentTurn that:\n1. Reads pending_urges.md\n2. Checks conditions\n3. For items that pass: creates a new one-time cron to actually push the message\n4. The push happens via that nested cron's delivery\n\nThe issue was: the parent cron's delivery was `announce` without a target, which failed. But actually, looking at the logic more carefully - the prompt says \"创建一次性 announce cron\" which means the actual push is done by a *new cron job*, not by this cron's delivery itself. So the delivery.mode of the parent cron shouldn't matter as much - the nested cron would have its own delivery.\n\nBut the parent cron was erroring because its delivery was set to announce without a target. We fixed that by adding the target. But actually, the parent cron doesn't need to announce anything - it just needs to run the logic and create sub-crons. The delivery should probably be `none` since the real pushing is done via the nested crons.\n\nWait, actually let me re-read the error:\n```\nlastDiagnosticSummary: \"Delivering to QQ Bot requires target QQ Bot target format: qqbot:c2c:openid (direct) or qqbot:group:groupid (group)\"\n```\n\nThis error is about the cron's delivery failing. But since the cron's purpose is to process pending_urges and create sub-crons, not to announce itself - setting delivery to \"none\" would be more appropriate. The sub-crons it creates would handle the actual announcement.\n\nBut I already set the delivery to announce with the target... that should work too actually. It just means the isolated session's output will be announced to the user, which isn't the end of the world - it might show the processing output.\n\nActually, let me re-read the cron prompt more carefully:\n\n\"满足的创建一次性 announce cron（delivery mode=announce, deleteAfterRun=true）推消息给对方\"\n\nThis means: for each urge that passes the check, create a NEW cron job with:\n- deleteAfterRun: true (one-time)\n- delivery: { mode: \"announce\" }\n- This new cron should deliver the urge's message to the target user\n\nSo the actual push is done by creating sub-crons. The parent cron itself just does the processing.\n\nSo the parent cron's delivery should probably be \"none\" - it doesn't need to announce its own output. Let me check what I set it to... I set it to \"announce\" with channel and to. That means the parent cron's isolated session output will also be announced to the user, which is probably not what we want - we just want the sub-crons to deliver the messages.\n\nBut 汀桑 is asking about the \"检查是否推送的逻辑\" - the check logic itself. Let me look at this more carefully.\n\nThe check conditions are:\n1. min_interval_hours has passed - so the same urge won't be sent too frequently\n2. The target hasn't spoken in the last 12h - so we only push when the person isn't already in conversation\n3. Familiarity >= 3/10 - don't push to strangers\n4. Only before 22:00 - don't push late at night\n\nThe purpose of condition 2 is interesting - it's saying \"only push when they haven't spoken recently\". So if 汀桑 was chatting with me all day, the urge should NOT be pushed because they're already in conversation. This was the right logic - the issue was just that no urges were being generated in the first place.\n\nSo 汀桑 is asking me to continue looking at the logic more carefully. Let me explain the full flow clearly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"你说得对，我重新仔细看一遍原本的逻辑，不只我刚改的那部分。\n\n从 AGENTS.md 和 cron prompt 里扒出来的完整流程：\n\n---\n\n### 原本的推送检查链\n\n**第一步：Dreaming 生成 urge（缺了这步）**\nAGENTS.md 5.5 写了要从 state.md 里挑念头写进 pending_urges.md，但 dreaming cron 的 prompt 没包含这步——所以 urges 根本没人写进去。\n\n**第二步：cron faye-pending-urges 每6h检查**\n触发后读 pending_urges.md，找所有 `status: pending` 的条目，对每条逐一检查：\n\n**条件A：`min_interval_hours` 过了吗**\n这条 urge 标记了至少间隔24小时才能再发。没到就跳过。\n\n**条件B：对方最近12h有说话吗**\n如果对方12小时内发过消息——说明ta已经在跟我聊天了，不需要主动推。这是对的——比如你今天下午一直跟我聊，即使有 urge 也不该在这时候发，因为没必要。\n\n**条件C：熟悉度 >= 3/10**\n太陌生的人不主动找ta说话。你的熟悉度8/10——这条肯定过。\n\n**条件D：**\n只在 **22:00 之前**推送。现在22:31，你已经过了推送窗口了。\n\n**第三步：满足条件的 ← 创建一次性 announce cron**\n不是直接发消息。是创建一条新的 cron（`deleteAfterRun: true`），由那条新 cron 负责 delivery 推送。\n\n**第四步：标记 delivered**\n推送成功后把 urge 状态从 pending 改成 delivered。\n\n---\n\n### 今天实际断的地方\n\n| 环节 | 状态 | 原因 |\n|:---|:---:|:---|\n| Dreaming 生成 urge | ❌ | cron prompt 没写这步 |\n| cron 检查 pending | ✅ | 触发了，但没东西可发 |\n| cron delivery | ❌ | 缺少目标格式，连报4错 |\n| 一对一 announce cron 推送 | ❌ | 测试过吗？没被触发过 |\n\n我今天一个主动消息都没收到，是因为 **urge 先没人写**，写了也 delivery 报错，两处全断了。\n\n我刚改的就是把这两处接上：\n1. dreaming 第6步补上了，明天06:00开始会有 urges\n2. 推送目标写死了你的 QQ ID——但要注意：那个 cron 现在是 `announce` 模式，它的输出会直接发给你，而不是静默处理再通过子 cron 发。要不要改成纯静默（`delivery: none`），它创建的子 cron 再负责推送？这样就不会把处理过程也暴露给你了🍧"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":101462,"output":2238,"cacheRead":3456,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":1654,"totalTokens":107156,"cost":{"input":0.01420468,"output":0.00062664,"cacheRead":0.00009676799999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014928088}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780151511602,"responseId":"8a304fc1-3ce8-4e7d-a981-f96e18567438"}}
